# Glowabetes

Glowabetes is an IoT project that connects Libre glucose data to a Raspberry Pi RGB LED indicator.

## System Architecture

Libre 3 sensor  
→ LibreLinkUp  
→ Docker uploader  
→ Nightscout (Render + MongoDB Atlas)  
→ Raspberry Pi  
→ Common-anode RGB LED

## Features

- Reads real glucose data from Nightscout
- Controls RGB LED on Raspberry Pi
- Supports terminal demo override
- Uses common-anode RGB LED
- Thresholds:
  - < 80 → Red
  - 80–120 → Green
  - 120–180 → Yellow
  - > 180 → Red

## Hardware

- Raspberry Pi
- Adafruit T-Cobbler Plus
- Breadboard
- 4-pin common-anode RGB LED
- 3 resistors (220–330 Ω)
- Jumper wires

## GPIO Pins

- Red: GPIO17
- Green: GPIO27
- Blue: GPIO22

## Notes

This project includes both:
- real sensor mode through Nightscout
- manual terminal demo override for classroom demos




